OL,6,F"The family of Sachin Hawkins now
OL,7,Fsuffer that pain each day, his life
OL,8,Fneedlessly taken.J"You initiated
OL,9,Ftrouble by being rude about Sachin
OL,10,FHawkins's choice of music, making, as
OL,11,Fyou did, a homophobic comment. He
OL,12,Fresponded verbally but with no threat
OL,13,Fof violence or intimidation
OL,14,Fwhatsoever. Physically, he was no
OL,15,Fmatch for you.
OL,17,F"You then viciously attacked him."JThe
OL,18,Fjudge said Mr Hawkins was "adored by
OL,19,Fmany" and his life was "precious and
OL,20,Fpriceless to his family members and
OL,21,Ffriends".
